<沿革內容><![CDATA[1.Formulated and announced in eight articles by the Department of Health, the Executive Yuan, under Wei-Shu-Fang No. 85010889, on February 14, 1996.
2.Amended and announced in eight articles by the Department of Health, the Executive Yuan, under Shu-Shou-Chi No. 0920001411, on August 21, 2003.
  The competent authority of this set of Regulations , which was originally "Executive Yuan Department of Health", was renamed the "Ministry of Health and Welfare" since July 23 2003 and the matters listed in Article 3 of the Regulations are then supervised by the "Ministry of Health and Welfare" and this amendment was announced by the Executive Yuan, Republic of China (Taiwan) on July 19, 2003, under Yuan-Tai-Kei Order No. 1020141353
3.Abolition of this set of Regulations was announced by the Ministry of Health and Welfare on February 20, 2017, under Wei-Shou-Chi Order No. 1060100082]]></沿革內容>
<前言><![CDATA[]]></前言>
<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This set of Regulations is formulated in accordance with the regulations of Paragraph 2 of Article 3 of the Act on the Prevention and Control of Child and Juvenile Sex Trade (hereafter referred to as the Act).
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Items included as part of “education and advocacy” in this set of Regulations, in addition to the items regulated in Article 4 of the Act, shall also include the following: 
1. Prevention and control of AIDS and other sexually-transmitted diseases.
2. Sex education.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The competent health authorities mentioned in this set of Regulations shall be the Department of Health, the Executive Yuan, at the central level; the municipal governments at the municipality level; and the county (city) governments at the county (city) level.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Competent health authorities at all levels shall conduct, in coordination with education, internal affairs, labor and other relevant organizations or civic organizations, educational and advocacy activities for the prevention and control of the child and juvenile sex trade.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 5</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Competent health authorities at all levels shall entrust civic organizations or academic institutions to implement, through various channels, by directly accessing sex trade-related work places, various educational and advocacy measures.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 6</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Competent health authorities at all levels shall, either by themselves or by entrusting medical care institutions, civic organizations, establish counseling service stations or counseling telephone numbers to provide relevant information mentioned in Article 2.  Children and juveniles who engage in the sex trade, or who may possibly engage in the sex trade, or who are victims of the sex trade, shall be referred for treatment or guidance.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 7</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Children or juveniles who have had their cases heard by the courts and have been found to have engaged in the sex trade or are likely to engage in sex trade shall receive lectures on the prevention and control of AIDS and other sexually-transmitted diseases.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 8</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This set of Regulations will be implemented on the day of announcement.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
</法規>
